## Key Insights

- **Python** emerged as the most preferred programming language across respondents, reinforcing its importance as the leading language in the data industry.
- **Data Engineers** reported the highest average salaries, while salary satisfaction remained moderate despite relatively positive work-life balance ratings.
- Survey responses were distributed across multiple countries, providing a broader view of global trends within the data profession.
- Organizations should benchmark compensation and employee satisfaction regularly, while aspiring professionals should prioritize in-demand technical skills to remain competitive.

---

## Tools & Technologies

- Microsoft Power BI
- Power Query
- DAX
- Microsoft Excel

---

## Dataset

The dashboard was developed using a survey dataset containing responses from data professionals across various job roles, countries, and experience levels.

The dataset includes:

- Job Role
- Country
- Programming Language
- Salary
- Salary Satisfaction
- Work-Life Balance Rating
- Age
- Survey Responses

> **Note:** This project is based on a publicly available survey dataset and was created for educational and portfolio purposes.
